What we are seeing is not the result of any diplomatic screw up by either administration but perhaps the about to become very violent spasms of a dying regime.  This was always a worse case fear.  NK so desperate to prop itself up that it sees a war as the only possible avaneu, no matter how thin the odds.  I have the strange feeling that THIS is coming very close to fact.  To a certain extent it shows our arrogance to assume that SOMETING we did, (under Bush or Clinton) led to this when it could have nothing to do with our policies and be soley related to internal NK troubles expressing themselves. <p><center><font face="lucida handwriting, arial" color="006800" size=+2><b>Radgen Waldjaeger</font></b><br><font face="tempus sans ITC, arial" color="675f00" size=+1><b>Semi-retired Pathfinder of Karana</font><br><font face="tempus sans ITC, arial" color="blue" size=+1>Shining Path</font></b><br><img src=http://radgen.homestead.com/files/tiger_run_md_clr.gif></center>
